[[火星|火星]]有兩個永久性的[[地理極點|極]][[冠|冠]]。在極區的冬天，極冠沉浸在持續的黑暗中，使得表面冷卻，並導致[[大氣層|大氣]]中25－30%的[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]][[凝華|凝華]]在表面成為板狀的固態二氧化碳（[[乾冰|乾冰]]）<ref name="icarus169">{{cite journal|author1=Mellon, J. T. |author2=Feldman, W. C. |author3=Prettyman, T. H. |title=The presence and stability of ground ice in the southern hemisphere of Mars|journal=Icarus|year=2003|volume=169|issue=2|pages=324–340|bibcode=2004Icar..169..324M|doi=10.1016/j.icarus.2003.10.022}}</ref>。當極區再次曝露在陽光下，冰凍的[[二氧化碳|CO<sub>2</sub>]]會[[昇華|昇華]] <ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Hess | first1 = S. | last2 = Henry | first2 = R. | last3 = Tillman | first3 = J. | year = 1979 | title = The seasonal variation of atmospheric pressure on Mars as affected by the south polar cap | url = | journal = Journal of Geophysical Research | volume = 84 | issue = | pages = 2923–2927 | doi = 10.1029/JB084iB06p02923 | bibcode=1979JGR....84.2923H}}</ref>。這種季節性的行動運輸大量的塵埃和水蒸氣，產生類似地球的霜凍和巨大的[[卷雲|卷雲]]。[[機會號|機會號]]在2004年曾經拍攝到水冰的雲<ref name="clouds">{{cite news|date=December 13, 2004|title=Mars Rovers Spot Water-Clue Mineral, Frost, Clouds|url=http://marsrovers.jpl.nasa.gov/gallery/press/opportunity/20041213a.html|publisher=NASA|accessdate=2006-03-17|archive-date=2012-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120224153628/http://marsrovers.jpl.nasa.gov/gallery/press/opportunity/20041213a.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

兩極的冠主要由[[冰|水冰]]組成。北半球的冬季，冰凍的二氧化碳積累為一米厚的薄層（相對於南極）；南極冠有厚約八米的永久乾冰蓋<ref name="darling_marspoles">{{cite web|last=Darling|first=David|title=Mars, polar caps|work=Encyclopedia of Astrobiology, Astronomy, and Spaceflight|url=http://www.daviddarling.info/encyclopedia/M/Marspoles.html|accessdate=2007-02-26|archive-date=2011-08-21|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/616WmSQ0r?url=http://www.daviddarling.info/encyclopedia/M/Marspoles.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在火星北半球的夏季，北極冠的直徑約為1,000公里<ref name="mira">{{cite web|title=MIRA's Field Trips to the Stars Internet Education Program|publisher=Mira.or|url=http://www.mira.org/fts0/planets/097/text/txt002x.htm|accessdate=2007-02-26|archive-date=2011-08-21|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/616Wm0v0n?url=http://www.mira.org/fts0/planets/097/text/txt002x.htm|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，並且包含大約160萬里立方公里的冰，如果均勻的分佈在極冠將有2公里厚<ref name="brown">{{cite journal|last=Carr|first=Michael H.|title=Oceans on Mars: An assessment of the observational evidence and possible fate|journal=Journal of Geophysical Research|year=2003|volume=108|issue=5042|page=24|bibcode=2003JGRE..108.5042C|doi=10.1029/2002JE001963|last2=Head|first2=James W.}}</ref>（相較之下，地球的[[格陵蘭冰原|格陵蘭冰原]]體積是285萬立方公里）。南極冠的直徑為350公里，厚度約為3公里<ref name="phillips">{{cite web|last=Phillips |first=Tony |title=Mars is Melting, Science at NASA |url=https://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2003/07aug_southpole.htm |accessdate=2007-02-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070224153145/https://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2003/07aug_southpole.htm |archivedate=2007-02-24 |df= }}</ref>。 估計南極冠和相鄰層狀沉積的冰總體積也在160萬立方公里<ref name="sci315">{{cite journal|title=Subsurface Radar Sounding of the South Polar Layered Deposits of Mars|author=Plaut, J. J.|journal=Science|volume=316|year=2007|issue=5821|doi=10.1126/science.1139672|pages=92–5|pmid=17363628|bibcode = 2007Sci...316...92P |display-authors=etal}}</ref>。兩極的冠都顯現螺旋結構，最近[[火星勘測軌道飛行器|火星勘測軌道飛行器]]使用{{link-en|SHARAD|SHARAD}}的雷達穿透冠的分析顯示，螺旋是由於[[科里奧利力|科氏效應]]的[[下降風|沉降氣流]]造成的<ref name="Onset and migration of spiral troughs on Mars revealed by orbital radar">{{cite journal | title=Onset and migration of spiral troughs on Mars revealed by orbital radar |author1=Smith, Isaac B. |author2=Holt, J. W. | journal=Nature | volume=465 | year=2010 | pages=450–453 | doi=10.1038/nature09049|bibcode =   2010Natur.465..450S| issue=4 | pmid=20505722}}</ref><ref name="Mystery Spirals on Mars Finally Explained">{{cite web|url=http://www.space.com/8494-mystery-spirals-mars-finally-explained.html|publisher=Space.com|title=Mystery Spirals on Mars Finally Explained|date=26 May 2010|accessdate=2010-05-26|archive-date=2012-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403180933/http://www.space.com/8494-mystery-spirals-mars-finally-explained.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

南極冠附近一些地區的季節性結霜導致地面形成1米厚的乾冰板。隨著春天的來臨，陽光溫暖了地下和來自下方的CO<sub>2</sub>昇華的壓力，抬高乾冰板並最終導致破裂。這導致火星[[間歇泉|間歇泉]]的噴發，並造成CO<sub>2</sub>氣體與暗色的玄武岩沙子或塵埃的混合。這個過程是快速的，在幾天、幾周或數月的觀察，就會發現這不尋常變化率的地質學  －特別是在火星。氣體在衝向間歇泉的地方，會在冰層下雕刻出一種類似蜘蛛狀的徑向通道<ref name="2006-100">{{cite news|title=NASA Findings Suggest Jets Bursting From Martian Ice Cap|date=August 16, 2006|publisher=NASA|url=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.cfm?release=2006-100|work=Jet Propulsion Laboratory|accessdate=2009-08-11|archive-date=2009-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091010164741/http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.cfm?release=2006-100|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Kieffer2000">{{cite web|first=H. H.|last=Kieffer|year=2000|title=Annual Punctuated CO2 Slab-ice and Jets on Mars|booktitle=Mars Polar Science 2000|url=http://www.lpi.usra.edu/meetings/polar2000/pdf/4095.pdf|format=PDF|accessdate=2009-09-06|archive-date=2011-08-21|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/616WmxuWK?url=http://www.lpi.usra.edu/meetings/polar2000/pdf/4095.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Portyankina">{{cite web|title=Simulations of Geyser-type Eruptions in Cryptic Region of Martian South|booktitle=Fourth Mars Polar Science Conference|editor=G. Portyankina|year=2006|url=http://www.lpi.usra.edu/meetings/polar2006/pdf/8040.pdf|format=PDF|accessdate=2009-08-11|archive-date=2012-02-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120217023905/http://www.lpi.usra.edu/meetings/polar2006/pdf/8040.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Hugh2006">{{cite journal|title=CO2 jets formed by sublimation beneath translucent slab ice in Mars' seasonal south polar ice cap|journal=Nature|first=Hugh H.|last=Kieffer|author2=Christensen, Philip R. |author3=Titus, Timothy N. |date=May 30, 2006|volume=442|issue=7104|pmid=16915284|pages=793–796|doi=10.1038/nature04945|bibcode = 2006Natur.442..793K }}</ref>。

